# Project config for home:Sakura286:test_package
#
# The whole point of the two repositories is that a spec may not name a flavor
# (openRuyi requires python3dist(...) rather than package names), so the flavor
# has to be chosen by the build context instead.  This is the OBS-side
# equivalent of pip's --index-url.
#
# Toggle these while watching the build results; that is the experiment.


# A4 showed these are load-bearing, not a tuning knob: comment them out and
# every name-free consumer goes unresolvable with "have choice".
%if "%_repository" == "rocm_build"
Prefer: python-faketorch-rocm
%else
Prefer: python-faketorch
%endif

# Semantics variant for the whole project.  Every build-time question needs the
# "identity" state -- with the rocm flavor stripped of python3dist(faketorch)
# there is only ever one provider, so Prefer: has nothing to decide and the
# expander just reports the Conflicts.  Comment this out to reproduce today's
# production semantics instead.
Macros:
%_without_distexclude 1
%_without_byname 1
:Macros
